parameters.name: MaximumPageSize
parameters.description: The ID of the MPS queue to which the snapshot jobs that you want to query are submitted. To obtain the ID, you can log on to the **MPS console** and choose **Global Settings** > **Pipelines** in the left-side navigation pane.

parameters.name: NextPageToken
parameters.description:
The end of the time range within which the creation time of snapshot jobs to be queried is.

*   Specify the time in the ISO 8601 standard in the
*   YYYY-MM-DDThh:mm:ssZ format. The time must be in UTC.

parameters.name: PipelineId
parameters.description: The start time for taking snapshots. Unit: milliseconds.

parameters.name: SnapshotJobIds
parameters.description:
The beginning of the time range within which the creation time of snapshot jobs to be queried is.

*   Specify the time in the ISO 8601 standard in the
*   YYYY-MM-DDThh:mm:ssZ format. The time must be in UTC.

parameters.name: StartOfJobCreatedTimeRange
parameters.description: The time when the job was created.

parameters.name: State
parameters.description: The information about the snapshot jobs.
